The course will give an overview of the structure and organisation of different educational texts. Students will learn how to search scientific literature, define terms and structure the material; use correct APA referencing; use correct terminolgy used in preschool and primary education; write an introduction. Theory is supported by practical assignments. Analysis of  various texts (scientific articles, students' theses). Independent work includes working with  electronic materials.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is develop student' academic writing skills in their field of specialisation as well as prepare them to compile scientific textsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course students should recognise the conventions of academic writing and be able to express themselves accordingly; have acquired theory and practice of creating academic texts; be able to find information from relevant data bases; write an introduction and abstract, use correct APA referencing and be able to write/format a course paper, bachelor's or master's thesis in APA style.
